  "why": "The paper performs diagnostic analysis of discovered failures by characterizing and categorizing adversarial and benign inputs according to model-internal uncertainty signals (single-shot PCS and multi-shot Bayesian VRO). It shows clear correlations between failure cases and these internal uncertainty measures (e.g., AEs tend to low PCS & high VRO; BEs high PCS & low VRO), and uses those correlations to generate and evaluate uncommon failure types and to explain why certain defenses fail. However, the paper does not trace failures to deeper underlying vulnerabilities such as corrupted/biased training data, spurious features, or overfitting — it stops at characterizing failure properties and their relation to model-internal uncertainty rather than identifying root causes in data or learned representations. This corresponds to a partial diagnostic insight per the metric (characterizing properties and correlating failures with internal signals), i.e., Medium.",
